Yes working, but not with any Red Hat

Red Hat OpenShift, Red Hat Ansible Automation Platform, Red Hat Integration

What's missing or what's needed in the solution.  Just high level description only.:
Red Hat value-adds can add provide a multi-cloud application platform with OpenShift to host Nucleus' technologies and services and provide ease and consistent in multi-cloud deployment environments, AAP can provide ubiquitous IT automation across on-prem and cloud services, and Red Hat Integration provides service orchestration and secured APIs to access services.

Executive Summary:
Both an automation platform and suite of products, NTT DATA’s Nucleus Intelligent Enterprise Platform has helped to automate hundreds of use cases. From building cloud-based application stacks to recreating the enterprise into a modern, integrated digital workplace. Yielding faster, higher quality, more-agile outcomes, Nucleus is the end-to-end engine for gathering insights-based services, identifying opportunities and the optimal deployment of resources — reducing costs and elevating performance. Built with extensibility in mind, Nucleus includes 30+ products designed in support of NTT DATA’s services to provide seamless, insights-driven workflow improvements for better outcomes. 
Nucleus automates data acquisition, processing, transformation and standardization across our clients and applications, to collate data-driven services into one cohesive platform—identifying opportunities that elevate performance. Easing the pain points of cumbersome manual tasks, Nucleus spans organizational boundaries and ever-evolving business processes, connecting multiple technologies to achieve end-to-end automation. Nucleus dynamically evolves to meet shifting requirements, supporting any combination of vendors and processes to continuously optimize service delivery performance. Monitored 24x7 by the NTT DATA Security Operations Center, Nucleus runs in a secure cloud environment protected by next-generation firewalls, Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) and multi-factor authentication for ultimate peace of mind.

Executive Summary:
Customers' cloud actions in the past 5 years or so are characterized by a fragmented approach driven by owned / leased data center closures (migration) or greenfield internet-facing app development (islands).  As these first phase projects are completed, customers are looking at deeper re-architecture to standardize and optimize these "cloud" postures for greater resiliency and efficiency.  The Multi-Cloud Initiative with Deloitte aims to achieve this based on OpenShift.  

Ideal Customer challenge/problems:
- Next-phase after "Lift-and-Shift" of VMs from on-prem to cloud - migrate to container format to reduce cloud resource consumption, migrate to container format for better integration with DevOps
- fragmented island of clouds - some apps, some migrated VMs, but little integration or unified design due to project execution
- mix of VMs and Containers that are not optimal - hampered by skills / procedures / practices
- uneven resiliency / continuity of workloads

Key Customer Benefits:
- Re-architect apps for efficiency after initial deadline-driven "Lift-and-Shift" to the cloud (range from easy VM to container migrations to strangling the monolith)
- Increase resiliency and efficiency between "on-prem" and cloud, and between clouds (e.g., DR / continuity)
- unified DevOps procedure and tooling to improve manageability

In Progress (same as above - with certain implementation details tailorable to customers)

Executive Summary:
During FY2023, I will be working with CACI on their CSfC Archon ZV Platform (CACI’s secure endpoint and data communication encryption suite) to test and migrate the Archon ZV‘s non Red Hat Linux based underlying OS to Red Hat Linux for ARM. This will be completed through ongoing co-creation meetings with CACI to assess the existing Archon ZV solution architecture, compatibility of the existing systems and applications to RHEL for ARM, and planning and execution for the migration of underlying OS to RHEL. This migration will require multiple joint planning and testing PoC’s to be conducted during the 1st and 2 half of Q2 of 2023. Archon ZV technical details are still to come, the majority of which are expected to be disclosed during our initial co-creation kick-off call with Dylan Connor, Archon ZV’s CTO and VP of Technology. In anticipation of our co-creation efforts, Gary Limon and I introduced CACI Archon to Red Hat’s Embedded Program.   
Why Archon ZV on RHEL for ARM Co-Creation is important for Red Hat: 
The Commercial Solutions for Classified (CSfC) program is an important part of NSA's commercial cybersecurity strategy to quickly deliver secure cybersecurity solutions that leverage commercial technologies and products. The U.S. government increasingly requires the immediate use of the market’s most advanced commercial hardware and software technologies within National Security Systems (NSS) to achieve mission objectives. NSA/CSS established the Commercial Solutions for Classified (CSfC) program and Mobile Access Capability Package (MACP) to leverage commercial products for layered solutions that protect restricted NSS information. Archon ZV Platform is approved for and meets the requirements of NSA’s Commercial Solutions for Classified (CSfC), Mobile Access Capability Package (MACP). 
For CACI, Migrating Archon ZV’s underlying OS to RHEL for ARM will result in a highly secure, stable, fully tested and supported OS platform. This in-turn will result in the increase in RHEL entitlement subscriptions sold to CACI under our Red Hat Embedded Program.   
Overview of the Solution: 
Archon ZV Platform https://www.archonsecure.com/secure-laptop is approved for and meets the requirements of NSA’s Commercial Solutions for Classified (CSfC), Mobile Access Capability Package (MACP), by building on a Dell Latitude laptop to create a zero-trust operating environment with customized security: 
High Assurance operating system  -A highly secure Linux based operating system serves as the platform for separate immutable virtual machines hosting captive portal, inner and outer VPN’s environment.
Internal Retransmission Requirements experience -Agency-specific cryptographic services and security policies are embedded in the hardware during the US-based factory process. Settings such as allowed tasks, edge network connectivity, and offline operation can only be changed over the air, not by users. We whitelist authorized tasks rather than black-listing prohibited tasks for a higher level of assurance.
Obfuscation of the user device and the destination server - Optional Archon CAMO software routes transmissions from the device through a unique multi-hop path each session, adding another layer of encryption at each hop. Adversaries monitoring traffic leaving the laptop can’t see the destination server; adversaries monitoring government servers can’t see the device at the other end of the connection.
Archon ZV mobile solution. It is a platform that combines security and reliability of a military grade secure operating system with the flexibility of a commercial mobility device.
The solution has passed CSfC requirements with the NSA. Archon enables high assurance operations and secures information so users can focus on the mission. The solution works beyond the internet connection and at the tactical edge.
Archon ZV is the world’ most secure laptop and is a turnkey mobility solution. With its NSA compliance, it can work across multiple domains and can be deployed straight from the factory in a matter of minutes, instead of hours or days.
The focus on simple and secure has allowed Archon to cover the last mile for the cyber-warrior and enable secure access to mobile resources across multiple domains. The Archon ZV laptop is part of a suite of Archon solutions that enable secure cloud connectivity virtually anywhere in the world.

Executive Summary:
Lockheed Martin Hardened Security (LMHS) provides a novel approach to ensuring the security and predictable performance of edge workloads. This custom hypervisor, built as a collaboration between Lockheed Martin, Intel, and Red Hat, is purpose built to present a low attack surface, and to ensure that multi-tenant workloads on an edge device are completely isolated from each other, both cryptographically and resource-wise at the hardware level.  
LMHS allows real-time and security-sensitive workloads to cohabitate on a single edge device without the risk of them interfering with each other, solving the problem of over-deploying hardware at the edge (where size, weight, and power are often limited) to achieve the same result.
This capability is ideal for any real-time and/or security sensitive multi-tenant edge use-cases, such as DoD tactical edge, 5G, manufacturing, heath-care and much more.     

What's Missing:
LMHS is operational today, and has been certified by Red Hat (link to catalog below).  What is currently missing are SKUs and an established channel in which to sell/distribute the solution.  Both gaps are in the process of being resolved at this time via conversations with existing Red Hat channel partners.

Describe sales process and if it will be partner led or co-sell.:
The sales process will likely be either partner led and co-sell.  We expect that our partners will position LMHS during their conversations with customers who are edge-focussed, and Red Hat sales teams will do the same.  Once a multi-tenant real-time/security-sensitive edge use-case is discovered, the conversation will naturally flow to LMHS, since it is uniquely positioned to solve both performance and security concerns at the edge.

Executive Summary:
Presidential Directives to secure the infrastructure and Edge have been published directed to be solved. "Both commercial and government organizations realize the old models of perimeter defense of a network are no longer sufficient. In the modern world, attackers are within the boundaries of networks, and yet systems and data must still be kept secure. Zero Trust is the answer to that conundrum and REDPro ZTX provides an implementable solutions to accomplish it. 
Additionally, US Government agencies, civilian and military, are mandated to move to a Zero Trust Architecture (ZTA) by 2024 per M-22-09, as well as other directives. Zero trust solutions are few and unproven, and most customers do not have the time or budget to develop their own ZTA from scratch. REDPro ZTX provides customers a solution to help them meet their security needs and USG compliance requirements. 
The ARMY, Air Force, Navy, the IC, the White House, the Health care market, Veterans Affairs and Financial Markets.
-Extensible, multi-level Zero Trust Security platform called REDPro ZTX 
-Leverages industry-leading Zero Trust, Data Protection, & Cyber Resiliency technologies
-Provides multi-level, hardware- and software-based monitoring & protection for Identities, -Networks, Devices, Workloads, and Data
-Enables ZT in DDIL (Denied, Degraded, Intermittent,& Low Bandwidth) environments
-Complies with industry best Zero Trust practices and standards (e.g., NIST SP 800-207, DOD ZT Reference Architecture)
"

For customers concerned about high availability of connectivity between endpoints and the REDPro ZTX Core offering, then the customer system infrastructure (e.g., Servers, storage) should be clustered in a three-machine configuration (high availability clusters). This deploys redundant message broker machines - so if one or two of these machines fail simultaneously, communication is preserved and thus the service is considered highly available.
The on-premise hardware or cloud system infrastructure is customer’s responsibility to
purchase/deploy and is NOT included in the REDPro ZTX Core offering annual subscription
